subSubSection.paragraph:
Pleuronichthys sp.
: Nakabo, 1995 : 204–205 [pictorial key and color photo; Japan (Maizuru)];
Kim et al ., 2001
: 156, 288, fig. 468 (brief description and color photo; Korea);
Kim Y. et al ., 2005: 288–289, fig. 490 (brief description and color photo; Korea )
.

Two lateral lines on each side. Lateral line scales developed but usually embedded subcutaneously. Main lateral line running across center of trunk to caudal base, curving gently upward before middle of trunk. Supratemporal lateral line (
SLL
) running along dorsal fin base, reaching middle of trunk (occasionally extending more posteriorly), curving downward sharply at supratemporal region (both sides, but often indistinct, particularly on ocular side), occasionally a short antrose branch from curve, running forward along supratemporal edge (Table 3).

A number of descriptions of " 

P
. 
cornutus

" have included lateral line scale (LLS) counts, that were consistent with the range of this species (
Table 5
), i.e., 100–108 (
Starks & Thompson, 1910
), 95 (
Wang, 1933
), 98–110 (
Norman, 1934
), 93–118 (

Okada 
et al
., 1935

), 93–118 (
Chyung, 1954
, 
1977
), 93–118 (
Okada, 1955
), 98–110 (
Zheng, 1962
), 92–102 (
Tchang & Wang, 1963
), 92–105 (
Fitch, 1963
), 97–103 (Ochiai, 1965), 97–103 (

Masuda 
et al
., 1975

), 98–110 (
Shen, 1982
, 
1984a
, 
1993
), 98–110 (
Chen & Yu, 1984
), 104 (
Matsuura, 1985
), 103–109 (
Miao, 1985
), 92–113 (
Chen, 1987
), 98–101 (
Xu, 1990
), 102–106 (
Lindberg & Fedorov, 1993
), 93–118 (
Kim & Kang, 1993
), 92–102 (
